http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Research-papers-invited/article13978127.ece

Karnataka State Tribal Research Institute, Mysuru, has invited papers from researchers, professors and students of universities in the State as well as NGOs engaged in research on tribal communities, for presentation at the two-day national seminar on ‘Participation of Scheduled Tribes in Indian politics: problems and prospects’ to be held from January 29 in Mysuru.While the last date for sending precise essays is January 15, lengthy essays can be sent by January 25. The essays have to be sent to the Director, Karnataka State Tribal Research Institute, No. 1540, Aniketana Road, Kuvempu Nagar, Mysuru.For details, call 0821-2560274 or 2560275, according to a press release.